            "text": "أَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام )"
          }
        ]
      },
      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:50:7",
      "text": [
        " أَنَّ أَمِيرَ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) صَلَبَ رَجُلًا بِالْحِيرَةِ ثَلَاثَةَ أَيَّامٍ ثُمَّ أَنْزَلَهُ يَوْمَ الرَّابِعِ فَصَلَّى عَلَيْهِ وَ دَفَنَهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Al Nowfaly, from Al Sakuny, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> that Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> curcified a man at Al-Hira, for three days. Then he<sup>asws</sup> brought him down on the fourth day, so he<sup>asws</sup> Prayed over him and buried him’."
        ]
      }
    },
